<!--
Project: Simple Responsive Website (index.html)
Instructions for publishing on GitHub Pages:
1. Create a new GitHub repository (public or private with Pages enabled).
2. Add this file as `index.html` in the repository root (or in `docs/` if you prefer).
3. Commit and push.
4. In the repository settings -> Pages, choose branch `main` (or `gh-pages`) and root `/` (or `/docs`).
5. Wait a minute and visit `https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/`.

This single HTML file includes inline CSS and minimal JavaScript so it's ready to drop into GitHub.
-->

